<br>
Black Steel is going to be one very contested spell.<br>
<br>
Another trouble for mages in particular is the sheer number of spells we have, and the relative rarity of mages with respect to many other casters.  There are fewer of us getting spectrals, and for each turnin there is less chance to get any particular spell, so it will take significantly longer for our spells to reach a 'reasonable' market value than most other classes.<br>
<br>
I do think that eventually the spells will be had by all -- but 'eventually' may be a long long time.  I would rather not wait a year for the tools that my class is balanced against.<br>
<br>
